- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the tool deals with network simulations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the tool can be used to evaluate performance at the algorithmic level. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the tool can be used to simulate and control dynamic networks. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper is not primarily about programming languages, but rather about a tool that uses Java as its language.
